1: China's 84% ​​tariff on the United States has been officially implemented since 12:01 today;
2: A whale address sold 5.04 million VIRTUAL at a loss of 3.48 million US dollars;
3: The MELANIA team sold 6.72 million tokens in the past 25 days and made a profit of 4.2 million US dollars;
4: Founder of Ethereum News Weekly: If ETH is not regarded as a currency, its value will approach zero;
5: LAYER hit 2 USDT this morning, setting a new historical price high;
6: OpenSea wrote to the SEC to request clarification of the regulatory positioning of the NFT market;
7: Binance's second round of voting for listing has ended, with UXLINK, ATH, and BIGTIME ranking in the top three;
8: A suspected Kraken co-creation-related address deposited 1,501 ETH into Aave and Compound;
9: Binance adjusted the step size of multiple spot trading pairs such as OM and XRP;
10: The Fetch.ai team is suspected of passing again DWF sold 15 million FETs;
11: An Ethereum OG address that has been silent for 2 years sold 10,702 ETH again;
12: Binance will launch the second round of voting to delist on April 10;
13: Binance announced the second round of "voting to delist" projects: 17 projects including FTT and ZEC;
14: Wayfinder will issue 5 million PROMPT tokens through Kaito Dashboard;
15: South Korea's five major banks called for relaxing restrictions on cooperation in the crypto industry and supporting an exchange to connect with multiple banks;
16: The U.S. Senate voted to confirm Paul Atkins as SEC Chairman.
